Janet Reno, the first female Attorney General of the United States, has passed away. She was known for her toughness and dedication to justice. Throughout her career, she worked on reforming juvenile justice, creating drug courts, and protecting children. As Attorney General, she prioritized transparency and accountability. Reno was admired for her intellect, integrity, and commitment to equal treatment under the law. Her legacy lives on in the lawyers she inspired and the impact she made on ordinary lives. The statement concludes with condolences from Michelle and Barack Obama to Reno's family and loved ones.